SPAIN DAYBOOK: Zapatero in Parliament; Inditex Earnings

-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s
-- 
2011-09-21T06:00:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/spain-daybook-zapatero-in-parliament-inditex-earnings.html
Prime Minister Jose Luis Rodriguez
Zapatero answers questions in Parliament in a weekly session
while  Inditex SA (ITX) , the owner of Zara, posted earnings that beat
forecasts.  ECONOMY:
*Zapatero and other ministers attend weekly question session in
Parliament at 9 a.m. CET
*Finance Minister Elena Salgado attends parliamentary committee
meeting at 4 p.m.  EQUITIES
*Inditex SA, the world’s largest clothing retailer, reported
first-half earnings that exceeded analysts’ estimates as
earnings before interest and tax rose to 914 million euros.
*Petroleos Mexicanos, the Mexican state-owned company, is
looking for strategic opportunities at a bargain price from
Repsol YPF SA after forming an alliance with Spain’s  Sacyr
Vallehermoso SA (SYV) ,  El Pais reported, citing an internal document
today.
*Iberdrola Energia do Brasil Ltda., the Brazilian unit of
 Iberdrola SA (IBE) , said it has offered to buy shares of Elektro
Eletricidade e Servicos SA from other shareholders after
obtaining a controlling stake in the company, according to a
statement to  Brazil ’s securities regulator.
MARKETS:
*The IBEX 35 Index rose 1.7 percent to 8,362
*The spread between Spanish and German 10-year borrowing costs
widened to 358 basis points.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
